-- Deutsche Bank hires former Luxembourg minister Frieden
-- By Maria Sheahan
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 10:15AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, July 10 (Reuters) - Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE> said on Thursday that Luc Frieden, 50, would join Germany's biggest lender to advise management on strategic aspects related to international and European affairs.

In his new role of Vice President, Frieden will also work with the bank's Government & Regulatory Affairs department and other infrastructure functions and business units, Deutsche Bank said.